    {
      "id": "PopularPost297255",
      "post_content": "@SRSFACE. You say this card is broken. So why should it be a rare? Would it be any less broken if it were a rare or mythic rare? Would you be happier if you had to pay $20 for a copy of this, a card which is clearly competitive? If it is broken, then it shouldn't have been printed at any rarity. The power level of a card should not be determined by its rarity. The reason it sometimes IS, is so they can sell more boosters because people don't want to pay $50 for rare playsets on the secondary market.  \n  \nI don't think it's broken, but because it's competitive I'm glad it's not a rare. After all, the charm cycle is all uncommon. The downside to this charm is that it's not as flexible as many of the others, as the direct damage and the double strike options will be more or less the same in the decks that want to play this. This means that this charm is less flexible than, say, [Azorius Charm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Azorius Charm), [Izzet Charm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet Charm), [Golgari Charm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Golgari Charm), ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Vandarringa",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost297255\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">@SRSFACE.  You say this card is broken.  So why should it be a rare?  Would it be any less broken if it were a rare or mythic rare?  Would you be happier if you had to pay $20 for a copy of this, a card which is clearly competitive?  If it is broken, then it shouldn't have been printed at any rarity.  The power level of a card should not be determined by its rarity.  The reason it sometimes IS, is so they can sell more boosters because people don't want to pay $50 for rare playsets on the secondary market.<br/><br/>I don't think it's broken, but because it's competitive I'm glad it's not a rare.  After all, the charm cycle is all uncommon.  The downside to this charm is that it's not as flexible as many of the others, as the direct damage and the double strike options will be more or less the same in the decks that want to play this.  This means that this charm is less flexible than, say, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Azorius Charm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Azorius Charm\">Azorius Charm</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Izzet Charm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet Charm\">Izzet Charm</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Golgari Charm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Golgari Charm\">Golgari Charm</a>, ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 297255)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '297255'); return false;\">\r\